text:
Digital payments, agentic commerce, and stablecoin policy debates drove the fintech conversation across Latin America this week:

Monetae agreed to acquire Transferencias de El Salvador to combine electronic money, bitcoin services, and digital assets on a single financial infrastructure platform

@mercadopago Developers launched Point Tap in Mexico, allowing SMEs to accept contactless payments directly on Android smartphones via NFC

@santander_br and @Visa completed a multi market pilot of agentic AI powered commerce across Argentina, Brazil, Chile, Mexico, and Uruguay

@MibancoCol  launched loan applications and deposit accounts through WhatsApp in Colombia, targeting more than 800,000 customers by 2026

Plus, Brazilian fintech and crypto industry groups pushed back against a proposed 3.5 percent tax on stablecoin transactions

Read the full LATAM fintech breakdown by Vivi Giacaman: https://t.co/w9mTkFhCqz

